### âš ï¸ **2-3 (DHCP Request - may not work reliably):**
```snort
alert udp any any -> 255.255.255.255 67 (
    msg:"DHCP Request detected: client requesting IP 192.168.1.100";
    content:"|35 01 03|";  # DHCP Message Type option (03 = DHCPREQUEST)
    content:"192.168.1.100";  # Hard-coded requested IP address
    sid:2000005;
    rev:1;
)
```

âš ï¸ **Needs adjustment.** DHCP requests **do not include the IP in ASCII.** Youâ€™re trying to match `"192.168.1.100"` as text, but DHCP uses **binary/hex format**.

ğŸ’¡ **Fix: Use Hex for IP**
```snort
content:"|C0 A8 01 64|";  # This is 192.168.1.100 in hex
```

âœ… **Fixed version:**
```snort
alert udp any any -> 255.255.255.255 67 (
    msg:"DHCP Request detected: client requesting IP 192.168.1.100";
    content:"|35 01 03|";
    content:"|C0 A8 01 64|";
    sid:2000005;
    rev:2;
)
```

